{"TopicId":161396,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How to conveniently balance VTOL engines?","CreatedByName":"drtricky","CreatedById":154647,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-01T04:26:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"drtricky","CreatedById":154647,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-01T04:26:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I finished a 17,000 ton flying battleship, and I want to fit \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engines on it for operational flexibility. One way to make sure the position of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engines are\u00A0balanced is by manually exiting and entering the hangar like a caveman, moving the engines around until the ship takes off perfectly vertically.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the way I balanced the engines for my first two \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E crafts, but this 300\u002B part craft lags my computer enough that repeatedly entering and exiting the hangar eventually causes the\u00A0game to crash.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy question is: Is there a more convenient way to make sure the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engines are positioned correctly?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FancyMouse","CreatedById":142946,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-01T05:10:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStock \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E build aid?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-01T06:17:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223075833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496291202\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154647\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022drtricky\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, drtricky said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a more convenient way to make sure the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engines are positioned correctly?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/33124-12-rcs-build-aid-v091/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E Build Aid\u003C/a\u003E all the way. Not 1.3 compatible yet though, AFAIK.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FullMetalMachinist","CreatedById":156531,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-01T14:41:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223075833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496291202\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154647\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022drtricky\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, drtricky said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a more convenient way to make sure the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engines are positioned correctly?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could also use TCA:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/97154-122-throttle-controlled-avionics/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t look like it\u0027s updated for 1.3 yet, however.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steuben","CreatedById":77368,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-01T16:58:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve had a bit of luck using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E and balancing the engine torque to near zero and/or adding \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E units to compensate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ForScience6686","CreatedById":144187,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T15:56:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCom and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003Ecot\u003C/abbr\u003E markers. \u00A0But you need to thrust limit your flying engines to get a true reading for your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003Evtol\u003C/abbr\u003E engines. \u00A0They need to be matched and your mass should not shift due to fuel usage our you\u0027ll have a hard time landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}